  {
    "id": "noscope-f75",
    "title": "Wire OS signal handler registration (signal-hook/tokio::signal)",
    "description": "signal_policy.rs computes correct decisions (forward, escalate, revoke) but nothing registers SIGTERM/SIGINT/SIGHUP handlers with the OS. No signal-hook crate, no tokio::signal, no sigaction anywhere in the codebase.\n\nintegration_runtime::forward_sigterm_then_escalate() manually calls libc::kill() but never waits for an actual parent signal.\n\nNeeded:\n- Add signal-hook or tokio::signal dependency\n- Register SIGTERM/SIGINT/SIGHUP handlers in the run mode entrypoint (main.rs cmd_run)\n- On signal receipt, call SignalHandlingPolicy::on_shutdown_signal() to get ShutdownDecision\n- Wire ShutdownDecision to AgentProcess::forward_signal() for child group forwarding\n- Implement double-signal escalation state machine (NS-028) at the OS level\n- Trigger revoke_all_on_signal() (NS-029) on shutdown\n\nRules affected: NS-003, NS-026, NS-028, NS-029 (all have policy implementations, need OS wiring)",
