    "description": "Distributed agent work queue pattern: each machine runs a polling loop (analogous to drain-beads.sh) against Provenance. When ready work is found, the agent claims it atomically, noscope mints a scoped Provenance API key via a provider script, the agent executes the task with only the permissions its scope grants, posts results back to Provenance, and noscope revokes the credential. Machines self-organize based on available compute. Requires: (1) Provenance API endpoint for creating scoped, short-lived API keys with specific permission sets (e.g., read-only on project X), (2) Provenance API endpoint for revoking keys by ID before TTL expiry, (3) a noscope provider script wrapping these endpoints, (4) a task readiness/claim protocol in Provenance (similar to bd ready / bd update --claim). This enables cross-team agent coordination without central dispatch -- an agent on Ben's machine can pick up work from Bob's project by minting credentials scoped to Bob's Provenance graph.",
    "projectId": "9887a770-ff7d-44d4-aeeb-a9c7b2252b73",
