Implemented the next steps and finished validation for `noscope-f75` signal wiring behavior in the integration runtime path.

- Reworked `forward_sigterm_then_escalate` to stop synthesizing shutdown behavior and instead run through real OS signal registration/processing (`SIGTERM/SIGINT/SIGHUP`) via `RunSignalWiring` in `src/integration_runtime.rs:360`.
- Added `forward_sigterm_then_escalate_with_os_signals` so tests can deterministically inject real parent signals *after handlers are registered* (`libc::raise`), while preserving the default no-signal path in `src/integration_runtime.rs:367`.
- Added timeout cleanup in the helper to prevent hanging tests when no shutdown signal arrives (sends `SIGKILL` after bounded wait) in `src/integration_runtime.rs:427`.
- Updated the existing escalation integration test to use the new helper with injected `SIGTERM` then `SIGINT`, preserving positive coverage for forwarding + double-signal escalation in `tests/integration_test_suite.rs:177`.
- Added dedicated NS rule tests validating no forwarding/escalation/shutdown path without real received signals in `tests/noscope_f75_os_signal_wiring.rs:16`.
